<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="157" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="157">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="157">
From the Latin word 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">aurantius</emphasis>
(= orange) and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">
<normalizedToken originalValue="pleurón">pleuron</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
(= sides). The name refers to the dorsal color pattern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
