<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="157" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="157">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="157">
This species is easily recognizable by its dorsal coloration and the gold sheen on the dorsal surface. The species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyperaspis panzosae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panzosae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">Hyperaspis panzosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gorham, but the specimen described by Gorham is a female and the author described the specimen having black legs (however, the figure in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Gorham’s">Gorham's</normalizedToken>
table has orange legs instead), while the female described here has only the basal half of femurs black; the author did not describe any sheen for 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. panzosae" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" rank="species" species="panzosae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">H. panzosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nestor-Arriola, Solis &amp; Toledo-Hernandez" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Brachiacantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Brachiacantha aurantiapleura" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantiapleura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">Brachiacantha aurantiapleura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a gold sheen on the dorsal surface. There are several species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyperaspis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">Hyperaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with similar coloration to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyperaspis panzosae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panzosae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">Hyperaspis panzosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
like 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. excelsa" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" rank="species" species="excelsa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">H. excelsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fall and 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. cruenta" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" rank="species" species="cruenta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">H. cruenta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
LeConte, so that without examining the original material there is no evidence to assume 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyperaspis panzosae" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panzosae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">Hyperaspis panzosae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Brachiacantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Brachiacantha" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">Brachiacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
instead of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hyperaspis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">Hyperaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; therefore, we decided to maintain 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nestor-Arriola, Solis &amp; Toledo-Hernandez" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Brachiacantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Brachiacantha aurantiapleura" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantiapleura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">Brachiacantha aurantiapleura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a separate species.
</paragraph>
